JOHANNESBURG - South African motorists can expect some relief at the pumps. The price of fuel is expected to go down end of the month. INFOGRAPHIC: Fuel price increases over the year The Automobile Association says the price of petrol is set to decrease by at least 41 cents per litre. Diesel will go down by 23-cents and paraffin will be reduced by 26-cents a litre. The AA says the country will need to stay attractive to investors if fuel prices are to remain stable this year. eNCA